Yes! The current situation is at a stalemate! However, our forces
still outnumber them. It won't be long before the tide turns in
our favor!

\SE[39]Well, I suppose that's how it will be. \SE[0]As
expected... It's a rather dull task.

P-Princess...! This area... is at its limit! If the defense line
collapses, there will be no escape...! Please make the decision
to retreat...!!

\SE[9]That's not acceptable!! \SE[50]If we don't buy time for
them, this war will end up being a pointless one!

H-However... If we continue like this, it will result in
annihilation. As the symbol of Ulysseene and as a leader, it is
your duty to protect your own life...! Princess... Please make a
decision...!

\SE[48]No, wait.... Those in positions of power... that's right.
\SE[51]Those are good words. I'll make use of them.

\SE[54]Chairman of the Cordin Magic Academy! \SE[50]I have a
proposal to make!!

\SE[54]Continuing the battle in this manner will inevitably
result in unnecessary casualties for both sides! \SE[35]There is
no need to needlessly sacrifice the lives of ordinary people!!

\SE[54]In other words... Let's settle this with a one-on-one duel
between you and me, leading our elite forces! \SE[52]As those in
positions of power, are you prepared to accept this challenge?!

There is no need to listen to such nonsense! The battle situation
is overwhelmingly in our favor! We should just crush them like
this!!

\SE[36]That's true...\. However, we will also suffer some damage
here. \!\SE[2]...You don't want to die just yet, do you?

I am prepared to sacrifice my life for the sake of the
country...!

\SE[42]Hehehe... It's not good to push yourself too hard, you
know? \SE[1]Well, it's fine. Either way, I will win. \SE[38]It
will minimize the damage to both sides. It's a win-win deal.
